PRETORIA - The Tshwane University of Technology has cancelled all face-to-face classes at its Soshanguve campus.
	
	The university cited continued disruptions by some protesting students as reason for calling off classes. READ: TUT announces no fee increases for 2017 Exams at the institution are expected to begin later this month. Last month TUT announced that there will be no fee increase for next year. Student protests erupted across the country’s universities after news that institutions can hike tuition fees by no more than 8 percent. eNCA